Okwoyo was officiating a match between Ichuni Junior and Aspire FC at Gesabakwa playing ground as the first assistant referee.The player who allegedly attacked his father leading to the unfortunate death was not playing for either of the two teams but had come to support Ichuni Junior. The family of a football referee who was allegedly killed by a player during a match have accused the police of failing to arrest the suspect.
Joseph Chang,aa Okwoyo, a 65-year-old ref, was punched in the face last week by the footballer after awarding a penalty during a local match in Kisii, leading to his death.



